PROSPECTUS FOR IEEE STANDARDIZATION

Proposed Working Group: IEEE 802.BC (Terrestrial Broadcast Data Services)

1.0 INTRODUCTION: THE GLOBAL OPPORTUNITY

Current terrestrial broadcast standards (HD Radio in the US, DAB+ in Europe, DRM elsewhere) are regionally fragmented and technologically stagnant. They focus primarily on audio delivery using modulation techniques from the 1990s.

The Phoenix Project (Recursive GFDM) represents a generational leap. By applying modern 5G-style waveforms (GFDM/FBMC) to High-Tower High-Power (HTHP) broadcast infrastructure, we can achieve spectral efficiencies ($>10 \text{ bps/Hz}$) that outperform all legacy standards.

We propose the formation of a new IEEE Study Group to standardize this physical layer (PHY) and media access control (MAC) layer for global adoption.

2.0 COMPARATIVE COMPETITIVE ANALYSIS

The proposed IEEE 802.BC standard offers objectively superior performance compared to existing global systems:

